From: Fix hisi_zip kernel panic by clearing SQE during QP creation
Subject: [FIX] Clear SQE memory to prevent residual tag data crash

Root cause:
- SQE memory is NOT cleared during QP creation
- Only CQE is cleared in qm_create_qp_nolock
- If DMA memory was used before, SQE may contain residual tag data
- If hardware generates interrupt before first request, callback reads
  invalid tag pointer -> kernel panic

Fix:
- Clear SQE memory when QP is created
- This ensures no residual tag data exists before callback is registered

Test:
- Apply this patch
- Run rmmod/insmod cycle multiple times
- No crash should occur

Signed-off-by: Fix Analysis

---
 drivers/crypto/hisilicon/qm.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/crypto/hisilicon/qm.c b/drivers/crypto/hisilicon/qm.c
index xxx..xxx 100644
--- a/drivers/crypto/hisilicon/qm.c
+++ b/drivers/crypto/hisilicon/qm.c
@@ -2158,6 +2158,7 @@ static struct hisi_qp *qm_create_qp_nolock(struct hisi_qm *qm, u8 alg_type,

 	qp = &qm->qp_array[qp_id];
 	hisi_qm_unset_hw_reset(qp);
+	memset(qp->sqe, 0, qm->sqe_size * qp->sq_depth);
 	memset(qp->cqe, 0, sizeof(struct qm_cqe) * qp->cq_depth);

 	qp->event_cb = NULL;
--
